comments: Ball (CHA) brings his left arm toward Murray's (ATL) path and marginal contact occurs with Murray's front as Murray drives toward the lane.
Williams (CHA) establishes himself in Murray's (ATL) path and absorbs the body contact during the pick.

Hunter (ATL) establishes his defensive position inside the LDB and, after Williams (CHA) leaves his feet to receive the pass, Hunter does not give Williams space to return to the floor when body contact occurs.
Williams (CHA) is in the lane for less than three seconds when the shot becomes imminent.
Hunter (ATL) slides his pivot foot prior to releasing his dribble.
Capela (ATL) and Williams (CHA) mutually engage and disengage with one another during the rebound.

Rozier (CHA) turns slightly prior to marginal lower body contact occurring with Young (ATL) on the wing. Rozier avoids making any further contact with Young as he brings his left arm forward toward Young's arm/side prior to Young's gather.
Capela (ATL) legally contests Rozier's (CHA) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
Washington (CHA) is jumping toward Capela (ATL) when marginal body contact occurs as they come together in the air before Capela's pass.
Young (ATL) commits a take foul on Williams (CHA). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Capela (ATL) firms up over his right foot and does not deliver illegal contact as he sets the pick on Rozier (CHA).
Ball (CHA) touches the ball last before it goes out of bounds.
Rozier's (CHA) right arm comes forward slightly prior to marginal contact occurring with the side of Young's (ATL) left leg as Young elevates for the jump shot attempt.
Washington (CHA) releases both of his hands away from Murray's (ATL) side and marginal contact occurs as Washington turns to roll.

Washington (CHA) goes to, not through, Murray (ATL) and marginal contact occurs as the two each attempt to establish post position. Washington and Murray then briefly remain engaged with one another as the drive simultaneously occurs.
Murray (ATL) and Ball (CHA) engage and disengage with one another, and marginal contact occurs during the inbound.
Williams (CHA) turns and initiates body contact that affects Young's (ATL) driving shot attempt.
Hunter (ATL) commits a take foul on Rozier (CHA).
Hayward (CHA) touches the ball last before it goes out of bounds.
Rozier (CHA) legally contests Young's (ATL) jump shot attempt.
Bogdanovic (ATL) commits a take foul on Rozier (CHA). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
